# Copy to /etc/forge-fleet/forge-fleet.env (mode 0600) and set values.
# Referenced by forge-fleet.service via EnvironmentFile=.
# Created automatically on first system install (install-update.sh / git-install.sh) if missing.

# Required when binding beyond loopback (see forge-fleet README).
FLEET_BEARER_TOKEN=change-me

# Optional
# When Caddy (or another reverse proxy) injects Authorization on loopback, set 1 so /v1/*
# still requires a bearer (see docs/CADDY-SYSTEMD.md).
# FLEET_ENFORCE_BEARER=1
#
# Admin “Update from Git” (POST /v1/admin/git-self-update): path to the **git clone** when the
# running tree has no .git (e.g. user install rsync’d to ~/.local/share/forge-fleet). Example:
# FLEET_GIT_ROOT=/home/you/forge-fleet
# Optional shell after successful git (instead of update-user.sh): FLEET_SELF_UPDATE_POST_GIT_COMMAND
# Optional: force admin "Update from git" behavior — user (default) vs system (/opt install shows root paste command):
# FLEET_SELF_UPDATE_INSTALL_PROFILE=user
# FLEET_SELF_UPDATE_INSTALL_PROFILE=system
# FLEET_LENSES_WORKSPACE_ROOT=/path/to/workspace
# FLEET_FORGE_CONSOLE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787
# FLEET_GIT_SHA=

# Telemetry (SQLite telemetry_samples + cumulative kWh in fleet_energy_ledger; optional)
# FLEET_TELEMETRY_INTERVAL_S=60
# FLEET_TELEMETRY_RETENTION_DAYS=730
# (0 = never delete old samples)
#
# Energy uses the same sampling cadence as telemetry. RAPL needs readable
# /sys/class/powercap/*/energy_uj for the service user; NVIDIA uses nvidia-smi in PATH.
#
# If nvidia-smi lives outside default systemd PATH (e.g. CUDA), set a full PATH (required keys only):
# PATH=/usr/local/cuda/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin
